  "local_port": 49576,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best date cake recipes?",
  "response": "Certainly! Here are a few popular and highly-rated date cake recipes for you to try:\n\n### **1. Classic Date Cake**\n**Ingredients:**\n- 1 cup chopped dates\n- 1 cup boiling water\n- 1 teaspoon baking soda\n- 1/2 cup softened butter\n- 1 cup sugar\n- 2 eggs\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1 1/2 cups all-purpose flour\n- 1 teaspoon baking powder\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n- 1/2 cup chopped walnuts (optional)\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Preheat the oven to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C). Grease and flour a 9-inch round cake pan.\n2. Place the chopped dates in a bowl and pour the boiling water over them. Stir in the baking soda and let it sit for about 10 minutes.\n3. In a separate bowl, cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.\n4. Beat in the eggs one at a time, followed by the vanilla extract.\n5. Gradually add the flour, baking powder, and salt, mixing until just combined.\n6. Stir in the date mixture and walnuts (if using).\n7. Pour the batter into the prepared cake pan and bake for 45-50 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.\n8. Let the cake cool in the pan for 10 minutes, then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.\n\n### **2. Sticky Date Pudding Cake**\n**Ingredients:**\n- 1 cup chopped dates\n- 1 1/4 cups boiling water\n- 1 teaspoon baking soda\n- 1/2 cup butter, softened\n- 3/4 cup brown sugar\n- 2 eggs\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 1 1/4 cups self-rising flour\n\n**For the Toffee Sauce:**\n- 1 cup brown sugar\n- 1/2 cup butter\n- 1 cup heavy cream\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Preheat the oven to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C). Grease and flour an 8-inch square baking pan.\n2. Combine the dates, boiling water, and baking soda in a bowl. Let it sit for 10 minutes.\n3. In another bowl, cream together the butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy.\n4. Beat in the eggs one at a time, followed by the vanilla extract.\n5. Gradually mix in the flour until just combined.\n6. Stir in the date mixture.\n7. Pour the batter into the prepared pan and bake for 35-40 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.\n8. For the toffee sauce, combine the brown sugar, butter, and cream in a saucepan over medium heat. Stir until the sugar is dissolved and the mixture is smooth. Remove from heat and stir in the vanilla extract.\n9. Serve the cake warm with the toffee sauce drizzled over the top.\n\n### **3. Date and Walnut Loaf Cake**\n**Ingredients:**\n- 1 cup chopped dates\n- 1 cup hot water\n- 1 teaspoon baking soda\n- 1/2 cup butter, softened\n- 1 cup sugar\n- 2 eggs\n- 1 teaspoon vanilla extract\n- 2 cups all-purpose flour\n- 1 teaspoon baking powder\n- 1/4 teaspoon salt\n- 1 cup chopped walnuts\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. Preheat the oven to 350\u00b0F (175\u00b0C). Grease and line a 9x5 inch loaf pan with parchment paper.\n2. Combine the dates, hot water, and baking soda in a bowl. Let it sit for 10 minutes.\n3. In another bowl, cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.\n4. Beat in the eggs one at a time, followed by the vanilla extract.\n5. Gradually mix in the flour, baking powder, and salt until just combined.\n6. Stir in the date mixture and walnuts.\n7. Pour the batter into the prepared loaf pan and bake for 50-60 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean.\n8. Let the loaf cool in the pan for 10 minutes before transferring to a wire rack to cool completely.\n\nThese recipes are sure to delight with their rich, moist textures and sweet, caramel-like flavors. Enjoy your baking!",
